<div class="elfsight-app-54d8cb68-4afb-4ebe-b139-2bd0bc687876" data-elfsight-app-lazy></div></div></div></section><section class="section"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer container-default w-container"><div data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cbf1" style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);opacity:0" class="inner-container _670px center"><div class="center-content"><div id="w-node-af088ac0-c61f-0ae6-a8c7-517ab41a5f63-b41a5f63" class="badge secondary mid"><div class="badge-icon-left secondary"><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6841ddf8ace3d9d9facb14fd/6841ddf8ace3d9d9facb1854_message-icon-property-x-webflow-template.svg" loading="eager" alt="Message Icon - Property X Webflow Template"/></div><div class="display-1">FAQs</div></div><div class="mg-top-small"><h2>Window Replacement FAQs </h2></div></div></div><div class="mg-top-medium mg-top-32px---mbl"><div class="inner-container _843px center"><div data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc02" style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 6%, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0) skew(0, 0);opacity:0" class="card accordion-card-v1"><div class="w-layout-grid grid-1-column accordion-v6"><div id="w-node-_7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc04-8b4bb9e4" data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc04" class="accordion-wrapper"><div class="accordion-item-wrapper first"><div class="accordion-top"><div class="text-titles"><h3 class="faqs-title">How much does window replacement cost in San Francisco?</h3></div><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)" class="accordion-icon-wrapper"><div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon-line vertical"></div><div style="background-color:rgb(20,22,28)" class="accordion-icon-line"></div></div></div><div class="accordion-bottom v1"><div class="w-richtext"><p>San Francisco homeowners typically invest $9,000 to $25,000 for a full window replacement project. The city's large stock of Victorian, Edwardian, and Craftsman homes often requires custom-sized sash and specialty glazing to match original profiles. Neighborhoods like Pacific Heights and St. Francis Wood — where homes sell for $3–5+ million — regularly see projects in the $25,000–$50,000 range. Oceanside neighborhoods in the Outer Sunset and Outer Richmond demand marine-grade specifications. Single window installation starts at approximately $750–$900.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="w-node-_7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc14-8b4bb9e4" data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc14" class="accordion-wrapper"><div class="accordion-item-wrapper"><div class="accordion-top"><div class="text-titles"><h3 class="faqs-title">Do I need a permit for window replacement in San Francisco?</h3></div><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)" class="accordion-icon-wrapper"><div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon-line vertical"></div><div style="background-color:rgb(20,22,28)" class="accordion-icon-line"></div></div></div><div class="accordion-bottom v1"><div class="w-richtext"><p>Yes. San Francisco requires a building permit for virtually all window replacements. Properties in historic districts — including Alamo Square, Mission Dolores, and Pacific Heights — may also need Planning Department approval to ensure compatibility with the character of the historic district. The SF permitting process is thorough; our team manages all applications, Planning Department submittals, and inspection scheduling on your behalf.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="w-node-_7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc22-8b4bb9e4" data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc22" class="accordion-wrapper"><div class="accordion-item-wrapper"><div class="accordion-top"><div class="text-titles"><h3 class="faqs-title">Which window brands does Deluxe Windows install in San Francisco?</h3></div><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)" class="accordion-icon-wrapper"><div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon-line vertical"></div><div style="background-color:rgb(20,22,28)" class="accordion-icon-line"></div></div></div><div class="accordion-bottom v1"><div class="w-richtext"><p>San Francisco's architectural and environmental demands call for the best. We most frequently install Marvin Integrity fiberglass-clad for Victorian and Edwardian homes needing superior moisture resistance, Andersen 400-Series for period-appropriate wood interiors, and Western Window Systems for contemporary homes in the Mission, SoMa, and Mission Bay requiring large sliding glass systems.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="w-node-_7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc32-8b4bb9e4" data-w-id="7c2f1aab-0a7c-7750-8c1c-d24e5259cc32" class="accordion-wrapper"><div class="accordion-item-wrapper last"><div class="accordion-top"><div class="text-titles"><h3 class="faqs-title">Does Deluxe Windows serve all San Francisco neighborhoods?</h3></div><div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)" class="accordion-icon-wrapper"><div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(90deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon-line vertical"></div><div style="background-color:rgb(20,22,28)" class="accordion-icon-line"></div></div></div><div class="accordion-bottom v1"><div class="w-richtext"><p>Yes — we serve all San Francisco neighborhoods including the Outer Sunset, Richmond, Noe Valley, Bernal Heights, Pacific Heights, Mission, Castro, Inner Sunset, Cole Valley, and all 94xxx zip codes.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="section-125"><div class="w-layout-blockcontainer container-default w-container"><div class="w-layout-grid grid-547"><div class="div-block-69"><div class="bottomfont w-embed"><h3 class="faqs-title" style="color:#fff;">Ready to Replace Your Windows in ?</h3>
